news.title: Over Rs 800 crore spent on Jammu smart city project in six Years
news.para: The chief minister said though no major complaints were received with regard to the completed work under the mission, minor complaints raised by people were promptly addressed.

news.title: Ulhasnagar civic body orders inquiry into alleged property tax corruption
news.para: Vadhrya alleged that officials granted a 100% penalty waiver on property tax instead of the 50% limit set by the scheme, benefitting a businessman. He further claimed that tax department staff tampered with the property tax software to facilitate this.

news.title: Development works and PMAY-G housing surveys underway in Nowshera, Jammu and Kashmir
news.para: The Line-of-Control in Nowshera previously faced frequent shelling, which made development work extremely challenging in this region.

news.title: Ranchi civic body intensifies its holding tax collection drive for FY 2024-25
news.para: Assistant municipal commissioner Chandradeep Kumar said "Over Rs 2 lakh were collected, two unlicensed businesses sealed, and notices issued to defaulters during a week-long campaign earlier this year."

news.title: Mt. K Kapital to launch Rs 2,500 crore fund for housing projects across major cities
news.para: These five projects, with a total developable area of 7 lakh square feet, are located in Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR) and are being developed by Keystone Realtors Ltd that operates under the 'Rustomjee' brand.

news.title: Over 700 houses in Gurugram’s DLF areas will lose occupation certificates for layout violation
news.para: The district town planner (enforcement), Amit Madholia, formally wrote to his counterpart in the planning wing, urging them to revoke the OCs of the properties on the list and instruct the DLF management to disconnect water and sewer connections.

news.title: Noida authority set to discuss uniform land policy, stuck projects on March 28
news.para: Among them is the review of developers' cases under the rehabilitation policy for stalled group housing projects, which is based on former bureaucrat Amitabh Kant's committee report.

news.title: Plan to turn four cities in Odisha into major growth hubs: Housing minister
news.para: They include the development of Bhubaneswar, Cuttack, Puri and Khurda as major growth hubs. Khattar also revealed plans for a new city in Greater Bhubaneswar area, with funding opportunities through the 15th Finance Commission and Urban Challenge Fund.

news.title: Odisha RERA fines builder over lack of proper parking space for flat owner
news.para: ORERA initiated a suo motu case under Section 63 of the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016, against the realtor for violating its order passed in Sept 2021 in favour of the complainant.

news.title: Soon builders performance, details of projects will be easier to track on RERA websites across country
news.para: All the real estate regulatory authorities (RERAs) across the country will have uniform websites and IT platforms for better navigation, which will enable consumers to get the project status of builders wherever they are developing residential and commercial projects.

news.title: MahaRERA stops hearing home buyer complaints in NCLT cases
news.para: Legal professionals say the regulatory body stops hearing cases and adjourns these cases, once it is informed that the proceedings regarding the project have been initiated at the NCLT.

news.title: Ananta Hotels & Resorts plans Rs 450 crore investment over five years
news.para: ​The company, which had recently opened a new 144-room resort at Ajabgarh in Rajasthan, is targeting tier-II cities for expansion with an eye on tripling its revenue from Rs 250 crore at present over the next five years, its Director Ashutosh Goyal told PTI.

news.title: Nine areas on Bhubaneswar outskirts to be brought under BMC
news.para: The proposal includes incorporation of nine areas such as Sijua, Raghunathpur, Lingipur, Nuagaon, Ebarang, Tikarpada, Itipur, Dhauli, and Basuaghai.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh govt pushes for cleaner cement production by using refuse-derived fuel
news.para: The initiative aligns with the Solid Waste Management (SWM) Rules, 2018, which mandate a shift from coal to RDF, a cleaner alternative derived from municipal solid waste.

news.title: Residents petition CM over Jaipur development body's patta issuance for Pratap Nagar colony
news.para: They asserted that although the JDA regulated the colony, Krishna Vihar, in 2007, the respective zonal office of the civic body remains unwilling to issue leases to these 80-odd residents, citing that a portion of the colony was reconfigured in the Zonal Plan in 2018 for use of govt activities.

news.title: Maharashtra budget to give further boost to real estate sector: CREDAI-MCHI
news.para: On March 10, Maharashtra Deputy Chief Minister Ajit Pawar, who holds the finance portfolio, tabled the state budget in the legislative assembly and announced a new industrial policy, focussing on Rs 40 lakh crore investment and generation of 50 lakh jobs.

news.title: Shalimar Paints focuses on rural pockets to tap growth: Kuldip Raina, Director
news.para: "If you look at rural markets today, only 30-40 per cent of the surfaces up there are painted. So, if that is the case, then the maximum growth in going forward is to come from rural markets only," he Shalimar Paints Director said.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh govt implements town planning reforms to facilitate stakeholders
news.para: Narayana took stock of the recent reforms initiated in the town planning with the realtors, officials and representatives of the licensed technical persons (LTPs) here on Friday.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Over 2,000 Tulsi Niketan flats set for a revamp
news.para: Developed on 7.8 hectares about 3 decades ago in the 1990s, the township lies in a dilapidated condition over lack of maintenance and repair over the years leading to disgruntlement among residents.
